        "user_id" : 2099297,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/08c1b800956f0b6953c06f880036e261?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "David",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2099297/david"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1650799318,
      "post_id" : 56995938,
      "comment_id" : 127203011,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I especially like this answer for two reasons. First it does not use exceptions for control flow. Second it is a perfect fit if you are working with a template engine and want to return a view in success case and NOT_FOUND in a failed case. If you are working on a REST API of course you should look at the answers returning a ResponseEntity."
    } ],
